				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Part 2 of the comprehensive bard issue list discussion is up.<a name="54329"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 29 04 3:36 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I don't see the point of maintaining three seperate lists.  Tremelo is maintaining a list of Top 10 Bard Issues.  If I understand correctly, you are refering to another (seperate) two lists.  I mean no disrespect, but I can't get behind that.
<br />

<br />
Bard issues are bard issues.  It makes no difference to me whether they are bugs or balance issues or wish-lists.  Issues are issues.
<br />

<br />
IMO, just keep one single list (like Tremelo is already doing).  As soon as an issue on the list gets taken care of, strike it off and add another issue.  Simple, short, sweet, and to-the-point.
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
